result.execSummary:
The defendant Scott A Kobs was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Manuf/Deliver Amphetamine(>3-10g), a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(e)2.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes: $290.60 fine/costs to be paid to Probation while on Probation.
May not possess or use firearms or body armor.
Cannot vote until civil rights are restored. Cannot hold elected office. Must abstain from all alcohol and drugs unless prescribed by a doctor and then must only take doses prescribed.

supervisions.notes: Must follow all rules of Probation. Entitled to 312 days sentence credit if revoked. Must complete all assessment and treatments as recommended by Probation.

timeConds.notes: **Per court order on 3/6/18, must serve 6 months conditional jail time beginning 3/5/18. Subject to Work Release per court order on 3/22/18.
